h2. Summary
When creating issues through REST API, if the description field contains an exclamation character the character gets escaped on Jira. This causes the editor to fail to renderr properly

h2. How to reproduce
# Make a rest api call for create issue with the body below.
{code}

POST Command: https://site.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/

{
	"fields": 
	{
		"project": 
		{
			"id": "10001"
		},
		"issuetype": 
		{
			"id": "10001"
		},
		"summary": "Testisng",
		"description": 
		{
			"type": "doc",
			"version": 1,
			"content": [
			{
				"type": "paragraph",
				"content": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Testing"
				}
				]
			},
			{
				"type": "paragraph",
				"content": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "!Testing!"
				}
				]
			}
			]
		}
	}
}{code}

h3. Expected behavior
An issue should be created with the description below
{code}!Testing!{code}

h3. Actual results
Issue is created with the description showing the exclamation character escaped
{code}\!Testing\!{code}

h2. Workaround
Currently none

I would like to be able to write a code block in Thrift. However, it doesn't seem to be supported, because when I preview my comment,

{code:thrift}
...
{code}

I see:

Unable to find source-code formatter for language: thrift.
